Nyeri Governor Mutahi Kahiga and West Pokot Governor John Lonyangapuo on Wednesday supported deployment of 100 Cuban medical specialists to all counties. They say the medics have achieved breakthroughs in diabetes treatment and eradicating malaria, will share experience and train Kewnyan doctors. “Let the government spread them around. We wilwork with them and learn from them,” said Lonyangapuo. Governor Kahiga said the Cuban doctors will ease the shortage of specialised doctors, build capacity and bring medical services closer to the people. Counties only provide a small stipend and housing. “As a governor, I really appreciate any help I can get from the national government in improvoving medical care,” he s